        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          I've said it before but I really like Madrid's midfield, it has a bit of everything. They don't smother possession like other teams (And have actually only once had more than 60% of the ball in La Liga this season, that being their last game against Osasuna, 61%) but they are by far the most efficient at creating chances from limited possession. 276 from 54% of the ball compared to 267 from 59% by Barcelona (using them as a direct comparison because only because they are in the same league, obviously). PSG did well last night but that was aided by Barcelona's performance so I don't see past a Bayern v Madrid final (draws permitting). Madrid would only have 30-35% of the ball in that game but could create more than enough. Whenever a team can create tonnes despite not having much of the ball, it worries possession-football teams because their largest weapon can be nullified. Madrid's efficiency is down to their midfield even though the individual stats go to the front 3.
